Pokedex: Even after Marill swims in a cold sea, its water- repellent fur dries almost as soon as Marill leaves the water. That's why this PokÃ©mon is never cold.

Name: AZUMARILL
Pokedex: These PokÃ©mon create air-filled bubbles. When Azurill play in rivers, Azumarill will cover them with these bubbles.

Name: SUDOWOODO
Pokedex: If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it's a Sudowoodo, not a tree. It hides from the rain.

Name: POLITOED
Pokedex: At nightfall, these PokÃ©mon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.

Name: HOPPIP
Pokedex: The eye motifs on its wings have similar properties to hypnotizing devices. It feeds off of dreams.

Name: SKIPLOOM
Pokedex: The "planteye" on top of its head releases a somniferous powder. This property is used in narcotics.

Name: JUMPLUFF
Pokedex: By flashing bright lights from its limbs, it causes powerful headaches that eventually knock out its opponents. It flies lowly in the night, hunting for people's dreams.

Name: AIPOM
Pokedex: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

Name: SUNKERN
Pokedex: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

Name: SUNFLORA
Pokedex: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

Name: YANMA
Pokedex: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

Name: WOOPER
Pokedex: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

Name: QUAGSIRE
Pokedex: Its body is always slimy. It often bangs its head on the river bottom as it swims but seems not to care.

Name: ESPEON
Pokedex: It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted, the orb grows dull and dark.

Pokedex: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

Name: SLOWKING
Pokedex: Miraculously, this former Slowpoke's latent intelligence was drawn out when Shellder poison raced through its brain.

Name: MISDREAVUS
Pokedex: It likes playing mischievous tricks, such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

Name: UNOWN
Pokedex: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

Name: WOBBUFFET
Pokedex: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

Name: GIRAFARIG
Pokedex: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.

Name: PINECO
Pokedex: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird PokÃ©mon that peck it by mistake.

Name: FORRETRESS
Pokedex: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

Name: DUNSPARCE
Pokedex: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

Name: GLIGAR
Pokedex: It flies straight at its target's face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

Name: STEELIX
Pokedex: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

Name: SNUBBULL
Pokedex: Small PokÃ©mon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

Name: GRANBULL
Pokedex: It can make most any PokÃ©mon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.

Name: QWILFISH
Pokedex: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent's size.

Name: SCIZOR
Pokedex: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor's body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.

Name: SHUCKLE
Pokedex: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

Name: HERACROSS
Pokedex: With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

Name: SNEASEL
Pokedex: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.

Name: TEDDIURSA
Pokedex: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

Name: URSARING
Pokedex: Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.

Name: SLUGMA
Pokedex: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

Name: MAGCARGO
Pokedex: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.

Name: SWINUB
Pokedex: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

Name: PILOSWINE
Pokedex: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

Name: CORSOLA
Pokedex: It will regrow any branches that break off its head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

Name: REMORAID
Pokedex: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

Name: OCTILLERY
Pokedex: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

Name: DELIBIRD
Pokedex: It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and PokÃ©mon, so it's always scrounging around for more food.

Name: MANTINE
Pokedex: Mantine lurk in the dunes, and can leap from their hiding spot in a fraction of a second to devour their prey.

Name: SKARMORY
Pokedex: Wild populations travel in groups lead by a single Skarmonarch who are protected by the Skarmory. They will ward off any invaders without mercy.

Name: HOUNDOUR
Pokedex: To corner prey, they check each other's location using barks that only they can understand.

Name: HOUNDOOM
Pokedex: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

Name: KINGDRA
Pokedex: With the arrival of a storm at sea, this PokÃ©mon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.

Name: PHANPY
Pokedex: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

Name: DONPHAN
Pokedex: An internal organ transmutes the outside moisture into warm water, which acts as a substitute to its blood in extremely cold temperatures.

Name: PORYGON2
Pokedex: After artificial intelligence was implemented in Porygon2, the PokÃ©mon began using a strange language that only other Porygon2 understand.

Name: STANTLER
Pokedex: Stantler's magnificent antlers were once traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this PokÃ©mon was hunted close to extinction.

Name: SMEARGLE
Pokedex: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.

Name: TYROGUE
Pokedex: Even though it is small, it can't be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.

Name: HITMONTOP
Pokedex: The energy of the Shiny Stone enlightened this Pokemon to never before seen levels of serenity. It is almost impossible to distract.

Name: SMOOCHUM
Pokedex: It waltzes around kissing anyone that it comes into contact with, while leaving nasty injuries that look like leech bites.

Name: ELEKID
Pokedex: It's not good at storing electricity yet. This PokÃ©mon sneaks into people's homes, looking for electrical outlets to eat electricity from.

Name: MAGBY
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day, Magby soaks in magma, resting and recovering from the day's fatigue.

Name: MILTANK
Pokedex: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it's been supporting the lives of people and other PokÃ©mon since ancient times.

Name: BLISSEY
Pokedex: Blissey lays mysterious eggs that are filled with happiness. It's said that anyone who eats a Blissey egg will start acting kindly to all others.

Name: RAIKOU
Pokedex: It embodies the speed of lightning. Its roars send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

Name: ENTEI
Pokedex: It embodies the passion of magma. Born in the eruption of a volcano, it can send up massive bursts of fire that consume everything that they touch.

Name: SUICUNE
Pokedex: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This PokÃ©mon has the power to purify dirty water.

Name: LARVITAR
Pokedex: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

Name: PUPITAR
Pokedex: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

Name: TYRANITAR
Pokedex: The quakes caused when it walks make even great mountains crumble and change the surrounding terrain.

Name: LUGIA
Pokedex: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

Name: HO-OH
Pokedex: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

Name: CELEBI
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon traveled through time to come from the future. It bolsters grass and trees with its own strength, and it can heal wounds, too.

Name: TREECKO
Pokedex: Quite skittish, its diet primarily consists of twigs and leaves. It mimetizes with the environment to escape danger.

Name: GROVYLE
Pokedex: The sheer power gained from evolution changed this Pokemon's metabolism, as it now behaves like an ambush predator.

Name: SCEPTILE
Pokedex: It can adapt to any and all environments, sitting at the top of the food chain. Because of this, they are an invasive species in most areas of the world.

Name: TORCHIC
Pokedex: Their immense ghostly energy allows them to summon additional limbs for a short time, but their inexperience makes them quite clumsy.

Name: COMBUSKEN
Pokedex: They blend in seemlessly with the shadows, which enable an easy ambush. When ignored, they will sometimes attack their own trainer.

Name: BLAZIKEN
Pokedex: Wild and unpredictable, their legs kick the life out of their opponents. The floating limbs disappear if they stray too far from the main body.

Name: MUDKIP
Pokedex: These Mudkips can be found sleeping soundly under frozen lakes. Their tails connect to the ice above, allowing them to sense vibrations from threats above.

Name: MARSHTOMP
Pokedex: Their icy blankets support their sleeping bodies and provide a shelter for small fish Pokemon. Unfortunately if they wander to close to its snoring mouth they may become a midnight snack.

Name: SWAMPERT
Pokedex: Its hibernation can preserve itself for years past the typical life span of a Pokemon its size.

Name: POOCHYENA
Pokedex: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

Name: MIGHTYENA
Pokedex: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

Name: ZIGZAGOON
Pokedex: It marks its territory by rubbing its bristly fur on trees. This variety of Zigzagoon is friendlier and calmer than the kind native to Galar.

Name: LINOONE
Pokedex: It uses its explosive speed and razor-sharp claws to bring down prey. Running along winding paths is not its strong suit.

Name: WURMPLE
Pokedex: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.

Name: SILCOON
Pokedex: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

Name: BEAUTIFLY
Pokedex: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.

Name: CASCOON
Pokedex: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

Name: DUSTOX
Pokedex: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.

Name: LOTAD
Pokedex: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

Name: LOMBRE
Pokedex: It lives at the water's edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.

Name: LUDICOLO
Pokedex: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates Ludicolo's cells, making it more powerful.

Name: SEEDOT
Pokedex: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

Name: NUZLEAF
Pokedex: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

Name: SHIFTRY
Pokedex: A PokÃ©mon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.

Name: TAILLOW
Pokedex: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.

Name: SWELLOW
Pokedex: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

Name: WINGULL
Pokedex: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea's edge.

Name: PELIPPER
Pokedex: Skimming the water's surface, it dips its large bill in the sea, scoops up food and water, and carries it.

Name: RALTS
Pokedex: Its black plumage is said to bring misfortune to others near it.

Name: KIRLIA
Pokedex: It uses wind currents to dance about in the night sky, even while hunting.

Name: GARDEVOIR
Pokedex: It has a latent power to read minds. A folktale tells that, long ago, this Pokemon and its "mirrored image" served a malicious king.

Name: SURSKIT
Pokedex: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

Name: MASQUERAIN
Pokedex: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction--to and fro and sideways.

Name: SHROOMISH
Pokedex: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

Name: BRELOOM
Pokedex: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

Name: SLAKOTH
Pokedex: If it eats just three leaves in a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.

Name: VIGOROTH
Pokedex: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

Name: SLAKING
Pokedex: It is the world's most slothful PokÃ©mon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.

Name: NINCADA
Pokedex: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

Name: NINJASK
Pokedex: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

Name: SHEDINJA
Pokedex: A strange PokÃ©mon. It flies without moving its wings, has a hollow shell for a body, and does not breathe.

Name: WHISMUR
Pokedex: When Whismur cries, the sound of its own voice startles it, making the PokÃ©mon cry even louder. It cries until it's exhausted, then it falls asleep.

Name: LOUDRED
Pokedex: The force of this PokÃ©mon's loud voice isn't just the sound. It's also the wave of air pressure that blows opponents away and damages them.

Name: EXPLOUD
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon can do more than just shout. To communicate with others of its kind, it'll emit all sorts of sounds from the holes in its body.

Name: MAKUHITA
Pokedex: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy PokÃ©mon that can withstand any attack.

Name: HARIYAMA
Pokedex: It loves to match power with big-bodied PokÃ©mon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

Name: AZURILL
Pokedex: Although Azurill are normally docile, an angry one will swing around the big ball on its tail and try to smash its opponents.

Name: NOSEPASS
Pokedex: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travelers check Nosepass to get their bearings.

Name: SKITTY
Pokedex: Skitty stalk and jump out at unsuspecting travelers from the shadows, terrifying them. In truth, they are very lonely.

Name: DELCATTY
Pokedex: Delcatty were once scorned as an omen of misfortune. However, in recent times, perception of them has changed, with them now being considered deeply dependable companions.

Name: SABLEYE
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.

Name: MAWILE
Pokedex: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

Name: ARON
Pokedex: When Aron evolves, it leaves behind molten pebbles. In ancient times, people would collect Aron's shed rocks to warm themselves.

Name: LAIRON
Pokedex: During territorial disputes, Lairon emits high amounts of steam. Close inspection of their magma armor reveals scratches and dents.

Name: AGGRON
Pokedex: The temperature inside Aggron's core can be compared to that of an industrial furnace. When threatened, it blows molten rock out of the pores on its back.

Name: MEDITITE
Pokedex: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

Name: MEDICHAM
Pokedex: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

Name: ELECTRIKE
Pokedex: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

Name: MANECTRIC
Pokedex: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.

Name: PLUSLE
Pokedex: It cheerfully spurs its friends on. The flames on its body shimmer and grow as it moves.

Name: MINUN
Pokedex: It hates seeing its friends get hurt. The water on its body glimmers in tandem with its mood.

Name: VOLBEAT
Pokedex: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.

Name: ILLUMISE
Pokedex: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

Name: ROSELIA
Pokedex: If threatened, it will barrage its opponent with heavy blows from its rock-solid arms, which are also full of toxins.

Name: GULPIN
Pokedex: There is nothing its stomach can't digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.

Name: SWALOT
Pokedex: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

Name: CARVANHA
Pokedex: It won't attack while it's alone, not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the PokÃ©mon attack as a group.

Name: SHARPEDO
Pokedex: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

Name: WAILMER
Pokedex: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

Name: WAILORD
Pokedex: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

Name: NUMEL
Pokedex: Ayreian Numel are rather peaceful Pokemon that get along well with others. However in a battle, the spores they spread are so potent that trainers are advised to protect their mouths and noses to avoid breathing any.

Name: CAMELLUM
Pokedex: Recent studies have found that these PokÃ©mon have the ability to communicate with each other through the spores they spread through a network hypothesized to be larger than the region itself.

Name: TORKOAL
Pokedex: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

Name: SPOINK
Pokedex: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

Name: GRUMPIG
Pokedex: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

Name: SPINDA
Pokedex: The chances of two Spinda having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

Name: TRAPINCH
Pokedex: While it may look weak in this larva form, it can shoot devastatingly powerful toxins from its mouth, used as a defense mechanism until evolution.

Name: VIBRAVA
Pokedex: The loss in power during this phase has changed Vibrava's metabolism, now only feeding on plants. They are very skittish and will most likely flee when threatened.

Name: FLYGON
Pokedex: Most active at night, their wings reflect the moon's light, attracting prey. The poor victim is dissolved into a puddle by this Pokemon's powerful poison and quickly digested.

Name: CACNEA
Pokedex: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

Name: CACTURNE
Pokedex: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

Name: SWABLU
Pokedex: Its cottony wings are full of air, making them light and fluffy to the touch. Swablu takes diligent care of its wings.

Name: ALTARIA
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon has a kind disposition, but if it's provoked, it will threaten opponents with shrill cries before attacking them without mercy.

Name: ZANGOOSE
Pokedex: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.

Name: SEVIPER
Pokedex: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.

Name: LUNATONE
Pokedex: Different types of music can be heard coming from it, depending on the mood it's in.

Name: SOLROCK
Pokedex: Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.

Name: BARBOACH
Pokedex: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

Name: WHISCASH
Pokedex: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything. If it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

Name: CORPHISH
Pokedex: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

Name: CRAWDAUNT
Pokedex: A brutish PokÃ©mon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

Name: BALTOY
Pokedex: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

Name: CLAYDOL
Pokedex: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

Name: LILEEP
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

Name: CRADILY
Pokedex: It has short legs and can't walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

Name: ANORITH
Pokedex: Anorith can swim swiftly by pulling its eight wings through the water like oars on a boat. This PokÃ©mon is an ancestor of modern bug PokÃ©mon.

Name: ARMALDO
Pokedex: After evolution, this PokÃ©mon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.

Name: FEEBAS
Pokedex: Although unattractive and unpopular, this PokÃ©mon's marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

Name: MILOTIC
Pokedex: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful PokÃ©mon of all.

Name: CASTFORM
Pokedex: It has the ability to change its form into the sun, the rain, or a snow cloud, depending on the weather.

Name: KECLEON
Pokedex: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

Name: SHUPPET
Pokedex: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

Name: BANETTE
Pokedex: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a PokÃ©mon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

Name: DUSKULL
Pokedex: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away ... or so it's said.

Name: DUSCLOPS
Pokedex: It seeks drifting will-o'-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.

Name: TROPIUS
Pokedex: A solitary Pokemon that resides in the depths of the jungle. It utilises powerful wingbeats to both fly and spread seeds, assisting the growth of its home.

Name: CHIMECHO
Pokedex: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

Name: ABSOL
Pokedex: Records released to the public just after the war state that Absol instinctively punished those that would bring harm to the forests near the conflict.

Name: WYNAUT
Pokedex: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

Name: SNORUNT
Pokedex: It attaches itself to the ceiling of volcanic caves to absorb heat, which it then releases to fly around.

Name: GLALIE
Pokedex: It can shoot concentrated energy waves from its horns. Its fire burns with a bright blue when it's enraged.

Name: SPHEAL
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon's body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It's faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.

Name: SEALEO
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon has a habit of spinning round things on its nose, whether those things are PokÃ© Balls or Spheal.

Name: WALREIN
Pokedex: Walrein's tusks keep growing throughout its life. Tusks broken in battle will grow back to their usual impressive size in a year.

Name: CLAMPERL
Pokedex: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.

Name: HUNTAIL
Pokedex: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

Name: GOREBYSS
Pokedex: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

Name: RELICANTH
Pokedex: Said to be an incredibly old species gone extinct, a few specimen have begun appearing near the shores of Ayrei. They look lifeless at a glance.

Name: LUVDISC
Pokedex: It floats about pretending to be dead, waiting for its prey to approach before attacking.

Name: BAGON
Pokedex: Bagon is a solitary PokÃ©mon that doesn't form groups with others of its kind. It also has a head hard enough to cleave a boulder in one strike.

Name: SHELGON
Pokedex: Shelgon ignores its hunger entirely, never eating any food. Apparently, Shelgon will evolve once all its energy stores are used up.

Name: SALAMENCE
Pokedex: While basking in the joy of flight generally keeps it in high spirits, it turns into an uncontrollable menace if something angers it.

Name: BELDUM
Pokedex: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum's sharp claws.

Name: METANG
Pokedex: Using magnetic forces to stay aloft, this PokÃ©mon flies at high speeds, weaving through harsh mountain terrain in pursuit of prey.

Name: METAGROSS
Pokedex: Metagross is the result of the fusion of two Metang. This PokÃ©mon defeats its opponents through use of its supercomputer-level brain.

Name: REGIROCK

Name: ZOROARK

Name: FERROSEED

Name: FERROTHORN
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

Name: CHESNAUGHT

Name: FENNEKIN

Name: ARAQUANID

Name: FOMANTIS

Name: SHIINOTIC

Name: SALANDIT

Name: SALAZZLE
Pokedex: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.

Name: STUFFUL

Name: BEWEAR

Name: BOUNSWEET

Name: STEENEE

Name: TSAREENA

Name: COMFEY

Name: ORANGURU
Pokedex: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded PokÃ©mon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.

Name: PASSIMIAN
Pokedex: Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation, the group survives.

Name: WIMPOD

Name: GOLISOPOD
Pokedex: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

Name: SANDYGAST

Name: PALOSSAND

Name: PYUKUMUKU
Pokedex: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

Name: TYPE: NULL

Name: SILVALLY
Pokedex: A solid bond of trust between this PokÃ©mon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

Name: MINIOR

Name: KOMALA

Name: TURTONATOR

Name: TOGEDEMARU

Name: MIMIKYU
Pokedex: Said to be a furious spirit that inhabited a popular doll. When said doll is damaged, the hatred of the specter takes form.

Name: BRUXISH

Name: DRAMPA

Name: DHELMISE

Name: JANGMO-O

Name: HAKAMO-O
Pokedex: Before attacking its enemies, it clashes its scales together and roars. Its sharp claws shred the opposition.

Name: KOMMO-O
Pokedex: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This PokÃ©mon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

Name: TAPU KOKO

Name: TAPU LELE
Pokedex: It heals the wounds of people and PokÃ©mon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

Name: TAPU BULU

Name: TAPU FINI
Pokedex: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

Name: COSMOG
Pokedex: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn't seem to care.

Name: COSMOEM

Name: SOLGALEO

Name: LUNALA
Pokedex: Records of it exist in writings from long, long ago, where it was known by the name "the beast that calls the moon."

Name: NIHILEGO
Pokedex: A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

Name: BUZZWOLE
Pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: PHEROMOSA

Name: XURKITREE
Pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: CELESTEELA

Name: KARTANA
Pokedex: This Ultra Beast's body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

Name: GUZZLORD
Pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: NECROZMA
Pokedex: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.

Name: MAGEARNA
Pokedex: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.

Name: MARSHADOW
Pokedex: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it's imitating.

Name: POIPOLE
Pokedex: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

Name: NAGANADEL
Pokedex: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

Name: STAKATAKA
Pokedex: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

Name: BLACEPHALON
Pokedex: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It's apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

Name: ZERAORA
Pokedex: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they'll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

Name: MELTAN
Pokedex: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

Name: MELMETAL
Pokedex: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

Name: GROOKEY
Pokedex: It attacks with rapid jolts of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more charged.

Name: THWACKEY
Pokedex: When it's drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won't even notice that it's already knocked out its opponent.

Name: RILLABOOM
Pokedex: Its ferocious drumming summons violent thunderstorms. It uses wind currents to direct its electric attacks.

Name: SCORBUNNY
Pokedex: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

Name: RABOOT
Pokedex: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

Name: CINDERACE
Pokedex: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

Name: SOBBLE
Pokedex: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokemon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

Name: DRIZZILE
Pokedex: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

Name: INTELEON
Pokedex: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

Name: SKWOVET
Pokedex: It eats berries nonstop, a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It'll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.

Name: GREEDENT
Pokedex: Common throughout the Galar region, this PokÃ©mon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.

Name: ROOKIDEE
Pokedex: Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied PokÃ©mon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.

Name: CORVISQUIRE
Pokedex: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent's strength.

Name: CORVIKNIGHT
Pokedex: With their great intellect and flying skills, these PokÃ©mon very successfully act as the Galar region's airborne taxi service.

Name: BLIPBUG
Pokedex: Often found in gardens, this PokÃ©mon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

Name: DOTTLER
Pokedex: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

Name: ORBEETLE
Pokedex: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it, and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

Name: NICKIT
Pokedex: They will create clouds under their paws and use them to float, blending in with the sky. They will often float up to mountains and steal eggs from bird Pokemon's nests.

Name: THIEVUL
Pokedex: Creating clouds under its paws, it races through the skies- swooping down below if it spots something shiny.

Name: GOSSIFLEUR

Name: ELDEGOSS
Pokedex: The cotton on the head of this PokÃ©mon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn, a Galar regional specialty.

Name: DUBWOOL
Pokedex: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

Name: CHEWTLE

Name: DREDNAW

Name: YAMPER
Pokedex: This gluttonous PokÃ©mon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

Name: BOLTUND
Pokedex: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

Name: ROLYCOLY
Pokedex: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

Name: CARKOL

Name: COALOSSAL

Name: TOXEL

Name: SINISTEA

Name: IMPIDIMP

Name: MORGREM

Name: PERRSERKER
Pokedex: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.

Name: CURSOLA

Name: SIRFETCH'D

Name: RUNERIGUS

Name: MILCERY

Name: ALCREMIE
Pokedex: A run-in with a mixer caused the cream to spiral. Those lucky enough to taste its rich flavour say it's to die for.

Name: MORPEKO

Name: DRACOVISH

Name: ARCTOVISH

Pokedex: Without a Dreepy to place on its head and care for, it gets so uneasy it'll try to substitute any PokÃ©mon it finds for the missing Dreepy.

Pokedex: Apparently the Dreepy inside Dragapult's horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.

Name: ETERNATUS
Pokedex: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this PokÃ©mon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

Name: KUBFU

Name: URSHIFU

Name: ZARUDE

Name: REGIELEKI

Name: REGIDRAGO
Pokedex: Its body is composed of crystalized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokemon.

Name: GLASTRIER
Pokedex: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength, and the mask of ice covering its face is 100 times harder than diamond.

Name: SPECTRIER

Name: CYNDAQUIL
Pokedex: It flares flames from its back to protect itself. The fire burns vigorously if the PokÃ©mon is angry. When it is tired, it sputters with incomplete combustion.

Name: QUILAVA
Pokedex: When it dashes through the night, one can see a trail of spirits following close behind it.

Name: TYPHLOSION
Pokedex: The spirits of the dead are attracted to Typhlosion. Their unrelentless ferocity have gained them the nickname "The White Wraiths".

Name: CHIKORITA
Pokedex: Said to have gone extinct shortly after the war, a few specimen have been found in the natural caves of Citrine Jungle.

Name: BAYLEEF
Pokedex: The many buds decorating this Pokemon's neck are a fashion icon in a faraway region. Records found after the war imply that this Pokemon may have originated from that land.

Name: MEGANIUM
Pokedex: These incredibly rare Pokemon form natural shrines in the secluded jungles they live in, adorning them with the pink leaves of their tail.

Name: TOTODILE
Pokedex: Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

Name: CROCONAW
Pokedex: Once it bites down, it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

Name: FERALIGATR
Pokedex: This Pokemon lives to fight, and it doesn't hold personal grudges. There's been multiple sightings of this Pokemon and Gyarados wrestling it out at sea.

Name: SHROOMISH
Pokedex: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

Name: BRELOOM
Pokedex: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

Name: HOOTHOOT
Pokedex: Friendlier and more intelligent compared to its Johtonian counterpart. It waves to humans and other Pokemon, hoping to study their reaction.

Name: NOCTOWL

Name: FERROSEED

Name: FERROTHORN

Name: GEODUDE

Name: GRAVELER

Name: GOLEM
Pokedex: Caves haunted by this Pokemon are off-limits to even the most experienced of trainers. Its spectral limbs carry it with incredible speed, surprising most.

Name: BUTTERFREE
Pokedex: It uses its enhanced brainpower to sense predators from up to 50 miles away.

Name: SWABLU
Pokedex: While cute and seemingly docile, it angers really quickly. They nest in areas most often hit by thunderstorms.

Name: ALTARIA

Name: SNORLAX

Name: GROWLITHE
Pokedex: The spirit of a loyal Pokemon has reanimated itself with a guardian statue as its vessel. It searches restlessly for something.

Name: ARCANINE
Pokedex: Ayreian Arcanines have a fierce sense of loyalty, and will willingly destroy their vessel to ensure their loved ones safety.

Name: MAREEP

Name: FLAAFFY

Name: AMPHAROS

Name: WEEDLE

Name: KAKUNA
Pokedex: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators underground.

Name: BEEDRILL
Pokedex: If faced with a stronger opponent, it dives underground before reappearing from below.

Name: SHINX

Name: LUXIO

Name: LUXRAY

Name: MAGNETON

Name: MAGNEMELT

Name: MERLICUN
Pokedex: It isn't considered very useful in any way what so ever. It seems to just want to crawl around and eat leaves.
